.TH stl_image 4
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Lstl_image\*O \- Software subset image data files
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "image data files" "software subset"
.iX "software subset" "image data files"
Each software product that is distributed as subsets for the
\*Lsetld\*O(8)
command has an associated
\*Vimage data\*O
file.  This image data file is created by the
\*Lkits\*O(1)
utility.  The image data file's name consists of the product's unique
3-letter name with the string
\*L\&.image\*O
for a suffix.  The image data file contains one record for each subset
in the kit.  Each record contains three fields separated by white
space:
.TP 13
Checksum
The modulo-65536 checksum of the subset file (after compression, if the
file is compressed)
.TP 13
Size
The size of the subset file in kilobytes (after compression, if the
file is compressed)
.TP 13
Subset name
The product code, subset mnemonic, and version number
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
The following example illustrates
\*LOAT.image\*O,
the image data file for a hypothetical kit:
.oS
15923    70 OATDCB100
24305   400 OATDCBDOC100
.oE
